to the editor re risk of arms race seen in us design of missile defense front page may 28 in the cold war the arms race between the united states and the soviet union provoked a buildup in china in response india maintained its nuclear option which in turn provoked pakistan to conduct a clandestine nuclear weapons program an american missile defense may now bring china and india closer strategically if they think a secure america will increase the threat of nato military interventions on humanitarian grounds to prevent suppression of violent secessionist movements the contrasting lesson from kosovo and chechnya is that nuclear weapons deployed on long range missiles can deter western humanitarian interventions raju g c thomas milwaukee may 28 2000 the writer is a professor of international affairs at marquette university

